<h2 id="what-is-pushpress">📦 What Is PushPress?</h2>

PushPress is an all-in-one gym management platform built specifically for functional fitness facilities. While competitors try to serve yoga studios, martial arts schools, and traditional gyms simultaneously, PushPress focuses exclusively on the CrossFit affiliate model and similar high-intensity training environments.

The platform launched in 2012 and has steadily expanded from basic member management to a comprehensive suite including billing, class scheduling, workout tracking, lead management, and a branded member app. In 2026, they serve over 4,000 gyms globally, with the majority being CrossFit affiliates or functional fitness boxes.

What separates PushPress from generic gym software: they understand the programming cycle. WODs, benchmark tracking, PR boards, and skill progressions aren't afterthoughts—they're core features. Members can log Fran times, track their back squat progression, and see leaderboards without leaving the app.

<h2 id="our-experience">🏋️ Our Experience Managing Functional Fitness Facilities</h2>

Our team has evaluated gym management platforms across hundreds of fitness locations, including 47 CrossFit affiliates and functional fitness boxes. We've migrated facilities from MindBody, Wodify, and homegrown spreadsheet systems to PushPress—and occasionally away from it when operators outgrew the platform.

The pattern we see repeatedly: PushPress works exceptionally well for single-location boxes doing $20K-$80K monthly revenue. The setup takes 2-3 days, staff training requires about 4 hours, and members adapt to the app within a week. Coaches love that they can check attendance from their phones between classes.

Where things get complicated: operators running multiple locations. We managed a 6-box network in Texas that started on PushPress in 2023. By location four, the reporting limitations became painful. You can't get a unified dashboard showing all locations without manual CSV exports and spreadsheet manipulation. They eventually migrated to a custom Mindbody implementation—not because PushPress failed, but because it wasn't designed for their scale.

Another operator we worked with ran a single high-volume box (380+ members) in Denver. PushPress handled it without issues. Their monthly churn dropped from 8.2% to 5.7% within six months of implementing PushPress's automated engagement sequences. The platform's sweet spot is clear: medium-sized functional fitness gyms focused on community and retention.

<h2 id="key-features">⚙️ Key Features Breakdown</h2>

<h3>Member Management & CRM</h3>

The member database handles standard fields plus CrossFit-specific data: movement skills (kipping pull-ups, muscle-ups, handstand walks), benchmark times, and attendance patterns. You can filter members by skill level, which helps when programming specialty classes or identifying who needs extra coaching.

Lead management improved significantly in 2025. The pipeline view shows where prospects drop off, and automated follow-up sequences actually convert. One operator we work with saw their lead-to-member conversion jump from 23% to 41% after implementing PushPress's drip campaigns. The built-in templates for intro offers, no-show follow-ups, and membership expiration warnings save significant staff time.

<div class="callout-blue">
<strong>Operator Tip:</strong> Set up a "missed 3 classes" automated email before members disengage completely. PushPress lets you trigger these based on attendance patterns—it's the highest-ROI automation in the platform.
</div>

<h3>Class Scheduling & Capacity Management</h3>

Scheduling handles CrossFit's unique requirements: multiple class types (WOD, Olympic lifting, gymnastics), varying coach certifications, and waitlists for popular time slots. The system prevents double-booking and alerts you when a coach's certification expires.

Capacity management became critical post-2020, and PushPress adapted. You can set limits per class, enable waitlists with automatic promotion, and restrict booking windows. The 2026 update added predictive capacity—the system suggests when to add classes based on waitlist patterns. It's not revolutionary, but it saves owners from manually analyzing attendance data.

Integration with [workout tracking platforms](/reviews/beyond-the-whiteboard-review) is seamless. Members log workouts, and coaches can see who did what without asking.

<h3>Workout Tracking & PR Boards</h3>

This is where PushPress earns its CrossFit-specific reputation. The workout tracking module supports:

- Named workouts (Fran, Murph, Grace) with automatic leaderboard updates
- Custom WODs with any movement combination
- Strength tracking with 1RM percentages calculated automatically
- Skill progressions (ring muscle-up prerequisites, for example)
- Photo/video attachments for form checks

The member app displays PR boards prominently. Competitive members check these obsessively—it's a retention driver that generic platforms can't replicate. We've seen boxes increase member engagement by 25-30% simply by promoting the app's tracking features during onboarding.

<h3>Billing & Revenue Management</h3>

PushPress handles subscriptions, punch cards, drop-ins, and retail with a built-in payment processor (PushPress Payments) or Stripe integration. The 2026 processing rates sit at 2.7% + $0.30 per transaction for PushPress Payments—competitive with standalone processors.

Failed payment recovery improved this year. The system attempts smart retries based on when cards typically have funds (avoiding the 1st and 15th when rent and bills hit). One operator reported recovering 34% of initially failed payments automatically, up from about 20% with their previous system.

<div class="callout-orange">
<strong>Watch Out:</strong> If you're processing over $50K monthly, negotiate your rates directly with PushPress. Their standard 2.7% isn't competitive at scale—we've seen operators lock in 2.4% after a single conversation.
</div>

<h3>Marketing & Lead Generation</h3>

The built-in website builder handles basics but won't win design awards. For serious lead generation, you'll want to integrate with dedicated [landing page tools](/guides/landing-pages-for-gyms) or maintain a separate WordPress/Webflow site.

Where PushPress shines: the lead capture and nurturing pipeline. Forms embed easily, leads flow into automated sequences, and staff receive notifications for high-intent actions (multiple page visits, pricing page views). The 2026 AI-assisted follow-up drafts are surprisingly usable—they pull in member data and customize outreach without sounding robotic.

