<h2 id="final-verdict">🏆 Final Verdict</h2>

PushPress delivers exactly what CrossFit affiliates need: functional fitness-specific features wrapped in a platform that doesn't require a software engineer to operate. The 2026 updates improved lead management and payment recovery—the two areas where previous versions lagged.

For single-location boxes and small networks (2-4 locations), we recommend PushPress without hesitation. The workout tracking alone justifies the cost when you factor member retention improvements. Our data shows 12-18% retention lifts for gyms that fully implement the tracking and community features.

For larger operators or those with complex multi-location requirements, PushPress works but requires workarounds. You'll export data to spreadsheets, build custom dashboards externally, and accept that unified reporting isn't coming soon.

The platform earns its position as the default choice for CrossFit affiliates. Competitors either lack the fitness-specific features (generic gym software) or overprice for the same capabilities (Wodify). If you run a functional fitness facility, PushPress belongs on your shortlist.

